To my way of thinking, that could go either way, depending on how Verant does things.<br>
<br>
In my experience, an evaccer is highly desirable - almost necessary - in a classic dungeon crawl.  Most of the people I hunted with in the early 50's wouldn't go into HS or the Hole without one.  If Verant remains true to that spirit, druids and wizards will both be highly sought after.  Unfortunately, I'm not sure whether that will be possible due to the instanced nature of these dungeons.  I would think they'd have to implement some sort of graveyard system - which makes the threat of a wipeout far less ominous.<br>
<br>
The other ability that used to be necessary in older-world dungeon crawls is snare.  If one runner got away in, say, Chardok, the group was in a lot of trouble.  (For some reason, in the newer expansions the mobs don't run much.)  If there are a lot of runners, then obviously snaring classes will be that much more desireable. <p>Bayler - Marauder/Deceiver - Xev<br>
Tessally - 54 Nun of Solusek Ro - Xev</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=natanmagus>Natan Magus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1028<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/03 1:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> Cough... SoS-Rogues... no need to have an evacer these days at all... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=laeyakk>Laeyakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/03 2:24 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> Want something concrete and less abstract than &quot;the game needs more death mitigation&quot;, &quot;the 2nd best healer in the game being half as good as the best is unbalancing&quot;?<br>
<br>
How about:<br>
Wizards get a 50% slow, 2 minute duration, 8 second casting time 10 second recast.  To be evil, add a 5/65 stun to the slow.  1 desease counter (ie, very easy to cure).<br>
<br>
Wizards vision line gains added 5% DD focus.  LoY one is L 65 cap.<br>
Wizards vision line made into a group buff, and doubled in duration.<br>
(your keen vision makes you able to hit with nukes a touch harder)<br>
<br>
Wizard familiars have a 20% to 50% chance of evacing a dieing groupmate of the wizard to safespot instead of dieing.  Range 100, and it kills the familiar (but not the buff).<br>
(a reason to keep flappy around)<br>
<br>
Xulz and Familiars both allowed to be up.  =p<br>
<br>
<br>
Shaman get a &quot;death mitigation&quot; buff that makes a player drop to 1 point of aggro (like Divine Aura), rooted and stunned for 1 minute, and lose all buffs instead of die.<br>
// Go go death mitigation<br>
<br>
Shaman get a group Topor at L 64 (500 mana).<br>
<br>
<br>
Necro rez changed to only consume the essence emerald 10% of the time.<br>
// More death mitigation!<br>
<br>
Monk gain a 10 minute reuse 80% rez at L 60.<br>
// Now we are talking Ghetto rez<br>
<br>
<br>
Bards get a 65% slow, dot, 2/65 second stun (3 ticks) at L 65<br>
// Bards become a primary slower.<br>
<br>
<br>
Druids and Clerics get a 200 mana 2 k &quot;30% mitigation&quot; buff<br>
<br>
1.0 casting time, 13 second recast time.<br>
30% of all melee damage to target is soaked until 2 k damage is soaked, at which point the buff poofs.<br>
1 minute duration<br>
L 51 for druids, 30% 2 k of mitigation<br>
L 55 for clerics, 20% 2 k of mitigation<br>
They don't stack.<br>
// There will be druid &quot;mitigation chains&quot;.<br>
<br>
<br>
Paladins LoH and SK HT reuse duration dropped starting at L 50 down to 10 minutes at L 65 with max AAs.  &quot;AA enhanced&quot; versions of HT and LoH left at longer durations.<br>
// More healing and death mitigation.  Paladins lose rez utility, gain LoH utility.  Mirror in SK required for envy reasons.<br>
<br>
<br>
Shamans and Druids get &quot;reincarnation&quot;, a 0% rez that does not prevent the target from being XP rezzed.<br>
<br>
Druids and Shaman get &quot;preserve corpse&quot;, resets the rez timer on a corpse to 3 hours (if it still has xp on it) and teleports it to zone safespot (if the target corpse's owner consents).<br>
// If someone dies, you don't have to stop xping.<br>
<br>
<br>
Kazad and PoC/9 upgraded to Aego-like duration.<br>
Ward of Gallentry made a group buff.<br>
Blessing of Reverence made into a group buff.<br>
// All horribly needed.<br>
<br>
Cleric nuke cost and casting/recast time dropped by 10%, and a -10 resist modifier added to the post 60 nuke.<br>
// Make Clerics better nukers, but MR only.<br>
<br>
<br>
Enchanters get L 65 Whisper of Morrel, a 8/65 stun, -30 resist mod, that places a 3 tick &quot;immune to Whisper of Morrel&quot; buff on targets who don't resist the spell.<br>
// WoM 2.<br>
<br>
There.  I've just doubled death mitigation in the game, improved healing for druids in a wierd way, and provided a few upgrades to other classes whose utility is reduced by the improved abilities of other classes.<br>
<br>
And yes, I would be ok with giving wizards rez or heals, other than it not fitting the game's theme very well.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bayler>Bayler</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/17/03 2:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> In the best non-evac case (i.e., everyone consents; nobody goes LD or AFK for a long period of time; the zone isn't *too* far from where the party was), you're ready to start again in 10 minutes.  That's time to get everyone to the zone, rez, regain mana, rebuff, and regain mana *again*.<br>
<br>
In a reasonable evac case (i.e., the tank dies and the crowd-controller doesn't think he can tie things down for a battle-rez), you're up and running again in 2 minutes.  That's time for the rogue to fetch the tank's corpse and the casters to med, and then rezzing and rebuffing the tank.<br>
<br>
That's for the mundane cases.  Other places I prefer evac to rez: The Hole (long way to drag corpses, over twisty pathes), Plane of Fear (if you didn't successfully break in, rogue CR doesn't help you much), ToFS (er, how do I drag through the mirror again?), Dragon Necropolis (%&amp;*#$&amp; wizard constructs!), Mephits in PoN (one-way, so you need to get your naked party to ZO2, or else wait for the graveyard).<br>
<br>
Oh, and then there's the small matter of level 18-62, where Shroud of Stealth isn't an option but evac is. <p>Bayler - Marauder/Deceiver - Xev<br>
